        <main class="docs-content">
            <h1>🚀 Getting Started with PaymentBot</h1>
            
            <section id="getting-started">
                <h2>What is PaymentBot?</h2>
                <p>
                    PaymentBot is a powerful Telegram bot that automates payment processing for businesses.
                    It allows you to accept payments, manage transactions, and track revenue all within Telegram.
                </p>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="number">1</span>
                    <strong>Create a Telegram Bot</strong>
                    <p>Talk to <code>@BotFather</code> on Telegram and create a new bot. Save the API token.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="number">2</span>
                    <strong>Configure PaymentBot</strong>
                    <p>Set up your bot token, merchant chat ID, and main group chat ID in the admin panel.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="number">3</span>
                    <strong>Add Payment Methods</strong>
                    <p>Configure your payment methods including bank transfers, wallets, and cards.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="number">4</span>
                    <strong>Start Processing</strong>
                    <p>Add your bot to Telegram groups and start accepting payments instantly!</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="installation">
                <h2>Installation</h2>
                <p>PaymentBot is a self-hosted solution. Follow these steps to install:</p>
                
                <pre><code># Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/paymentbot.git

# Install dependencies
cd paymentbot
npm install

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env

# Start the application
npm run dev</code></pre>
                
                <p>Visit <code>http://localhost:3000</code> to access the admin dashboard.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="configuration">
                <h2>Configuration</h2>
                <p>Configure your <code>.env</code> file with the following variables:</p>
                
                <pre><code># Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/paymentbot

# Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
MERCHANT_CHAT_ID=your_merchant_chat_id
MAIN_GROUP_CHAT_ID=your_main_group_chat_id

# Admin
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD=your_secure_password

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key</code></pre>
            </section>

            <section id="bot-setup">
                <h2>Bot Setup</h2>
                <h3>Create a Bot</h3>
                <p>1. Go to <a href="/admin/bots" style="color:#60a5fa;">Bot Management</a></p>
                <p>2. Click <strong>"Add Bot"</strong></p>
                <p>3. Enter your bot name and token</p>
                <p>4. Select a plan and configure settings</p>
                
                <h3>Bot Commands</h3>
                <ul style="color:#94a3b8; padding-left:1.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">
                    <li><code>/start</code> - Welcome message and main menu</li>
                    <li><code>/help</code> - How to use the bot</li>
                    <li><code>/status</code> - Check bot status</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="payment-methods">
                <h2>Payment Methods</h2>
                <p>PaymentBot supports multiple payment methods:</p>
                
                <ul style="color:#94a3b8; padding-left:1.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">
                    <li>🏦 <strong>Bank Transfer</strong> - Traditional bank transfers</li>
                    <li>📱 <strong>Digital Wallet</strong> - E-wallet payments</li>
                    <li>💳 <strong>Card Payment</strong> - Direct card payments</li>
                    <li>🏧 <strong>Cash Deposit</strong> - In-person cash deposits</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p>Each payment method can be configured with custom instructions, QR codes, and bank details.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="admin-dashboard">
                <h2>Admin Dashboard</h2>
                <p>The admin dashboard provides complete control over your payment system:</p>
                
                <ul style="color:#94a3b8; padding-left:1.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">
                    <li>📊 <strong>Analytics</strong> - View transaction statistics</li>
                    <li>🤖 <strong>Bot Management</strong> - Manage multiple bots</li>
                    <li>💳 <strong>Payment Methods</strong> - Configure payment options</li>
                    <li>📋 <strong>Transactions</strong> - View and manage transactions</li>
                    <li>👥 <strong>User Management</strong> - Manage admin users</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="faq">
                <h2>FAQ</h2>
                
                <h3>How do I get my chat ID?</h3>
                <p>Talk to <code>@userinfobot</code> on Telegram to get your user ID. For group IDs, add <code>@getidsbot</code> to your group.</p>
                
                <h3>Can I use multiple bots?</h3>
                <p>Yes! PaymentBot supports multiple bots with different configurations and payment methods.</p>
                
                <h3>How secure is PaymentBot?</h3>
                <p>PaymentBot uses JWT authentication, encrypted sessions, and follows security best practices for payment processing.</p>
                
                <h3>Do I need coding skills?</h3>
                <p>No! PaymentBot comes with a user-friendly admin dashboard. No coding required for basic setup and management.</p>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>

